Grove School is a Pre-Kindergarten through Eighth Grade Public Elementary School District located in Shawnee, Oklahoma. Grove School has been a leader in educating students in Pottawatomie County since 1893! Located on the outskirts of Shawnee, Oklahoma, our community school sits on twelve acres. Grove School provides rigorous, full day educational programs for ten grade levels, four-year-olds through eighth grade, while maintaining a small school, nurturing environment. The current student population is approximately 550, allowing for a teacher to student ratio of approximately 1:19. With a staff of highly qualified and caring individuals, Grove School provides a safe educational environment with high academic expectations for student success. 














